{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014eVzdc2JysUVec9gECgzga","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/commands/\n     2→\n     3→CLI command implementations for the `codeharness` tool. Each file exports a `register*Command(program)` function that adds a command (or command group) to the Commander program instance. All commands are registered in `src/index.ts`.\n     4→\n     5→## Commands\n     6→\n     7→### init.ts\n     8→Initializes the harness in a project. Detects stack (Node.js/Python) and app type, installs dependencies, sets up Beads issue tracking, installs BMAD with patches, creates state file, scaffolds AGENTS.md and docs/, instruments OTLP, and starts the Docker observability stack.\n     9→- **Key deps:** `lib/stack-detect`, `lib/state`, `lib/deps`, `lib/beads`, `lib/bmad`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/templates`, `lib/stack-path`\n    10→- **Subcommands:** none (single action)\n    11→\n    12→### bridge.ts\n    13→Bridges BMAD epics/stories into the Beads task store. Parses a BMAD epics markdown file, extracts stories with acceptance criteria, and imports them as Beads issues with deduplication.\n    14→- **Key deps:** `lib/bmad` (parser), `lib/beads` (issue creation), `lib/output`\n    15→- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epics <path>`, supports `--dry-run`\n    16→\n    17→### run.ts\n    18→Executes the autonomous coding loop. Pre-flight checks: plugin directory, state reconciliation, Docker availability (`isDockerAvailable()`), and orphan container cleanup (`cleanupContainers()`). Then reads sprint status, generates Ralph prompt, and spawns the agent driver with configurable iteration limits, timeouts, and retry counts. Pipes agent stdout/stderr through `driver.parseOutput()` into the Ink renderer.\n    19→- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (isDockerAvailable), `modules/infra` (cleanupContainers), `modules/sprint` (readSprintStatusFromState, reconcileState, getSprintState), `lib/agents` (getDriver), `lib/ink-renderer` (startRenderer), `lib/output`\n    20→- **Exports:** `resolvePluginDir()`, `countStories` (re-export from run-helpers), `registerRunCommand(program)`\n    21→- **Subcommands:** none (single action with many options)\n    22→\n    23→### verify.ts\n    24→Runs the verification pipeline on completed work. Two modes: (1) story verification via `--story <id>` — parses acceptance criteria, checks preconditions, validates proof quality (rejects proofs with PENDING ACs), creates proof document, runs Showboat verify, updates state, closes Beads issue, moves exec-plan to completed; (2) retrospective verification via `--retro --epic <n>` — checks that `epic-N-retrospective.md` exists, marks it done in sprint-status.yaml. JSON output includes `proofQuality` metrics.\n    25→- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (parseStoryACs, validateProofQuality, checkPreconditions, etc.), `lib/doc-health` (exec-plan completion), `lib/beads-sync` (sprint status for retro)\n    26→- **Flags:** `--story <id>` (story mode), `--retro` + `--epic <n>` (retro mode), `--json`\n    27→\n    28→### status.ts\n    29→Displays current harness status and health. Shows version, stack, enforcement settings, Docker/observability state (mode-aware: local-shared, remote-direct, remote-routed), Beads summary, onboarding progress, session flags, coverage, and verification log. Supports `--check` for pass/fail health checks.\n    30→- **Key deps:** `lib/docker`, `lib/state`, `lib/beads`, `lib/onboard-checks`, `lib/stack-path`\n    31→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-docker`, `--check`\n    32→\n    33→### onboard.ts\n    34→Alias for `audit` (FR16). Delegates all behavior to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler, ensuring identical output. Provides a deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints a warning before running audit.\n    35→- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit), `lib/output` (warn)\n    36→- **Exports:** `registerOnboardCommand(program)`\n    37→- **Subcommands:** `scan` (deprecated, prints warning then runs audit)\n    38→\n    39→### audit-action.ts\n    40→Shared audit action handler used by both `audit.ts` and `onboard.ts`. Contains the full audit execution logic: precondition checks, `runAudit()`, `--fix` handling (generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), and output formatting (human and JSON).\n    41→- **Key deps:** `modules/audit` (runAudit, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), `modules/audit/report` (formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson), `lib/onboard-checks` (runPreconditions), `lib/output`\n    42→- **Exports:** `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean })`\n    43→\n    44→### teardown.ts\n    45→Removes the harness from a project. Stops Docker containers (mode-aware), removes BMAD patches, cleans OTLP instrumented scripts from package.json, deletes state file and .harness/ cache. Preserves .beads/, _bmad/, and docs/ by default.\n    46→- **Key deps:** `lib/state`, `lib/bmad` (PATCH_TARGETS), `lib/patch-engine`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/stack-path`\n    47→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--keep-docker`, `--keep-beads`\n    48→\n    49→### state.ts\n    50→Manages harness state via subcommands. Provides read/write access to the YAML frontmatter state file using dot-notation keys.\n    51→- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (read/write/get/set), `yaml` (stringify for display)\n    52→- **Subcommands:** `show`, `get <key>`, `set <key> <value>`, `reset-session`\n    53→\n    54→### sync.ts\n    55→Synchronizes Beads issue statuses with story files and sprint-status.yaml. Supports bidirectional, beads-to-files, and files-to-beads directions. Can sync a single story or all stories.\n    56→- **Key deps:** `lib/beads` (issue CRUD), `lib/beads-sync` (sync logic)\n    57→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--direction <dir>`, `--story <key>`\n    58→\n    59→### coverage.ts\n    60→Runs tests with coverage measurement and evaluates results against targets. Detects the coverage tool (c8/coverage.py), runs or checks coverage, evaluates against project target, checks per-file coverage floors, and updates state.\n    61→- **Key deps:** `lib/coverage` (detection, execution, evaluation)\n    62→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-only`, `--story <id>`, `--min-file <percent>`\n    63→\n    64→### doc-health.ts\n    65→Scans documentation for freshness and quality issues. Checks whether AGENTS.md files and other docs are stale relative to their associated source code. Can scope checks to modules changed by a specific story.\n    66→- **Key deps:** `lib/doc-health` (scanning, freshness checks)\n    67→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <id>`, `--fix` (placeholder)\n    68→\n    69→### stack.ts\n    70→Manages the shared observability stack (Docker-based). Starts, stops, and shows status of the VictoriaMetrics/OTel Collector stack. Mode-aware: handles local-shared, remote-direct, and remote-routed configurations.\n    71→- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (stack lifecycle), `lib/state`, `lib/stack-path`\n    72→- **Subcommands:** `start`, `stop`, `status`\n    73→\n    74→### retro-import.ts\n    75→Imports retrospective action items as beads issues. Parses `epic-N-retrospective.md` for action item tables, classifies each item (harness/tool/project), derives priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids.\n    76→- **Key deps:** `lib/retro-parser` (parsing, classification, priority), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n    77→- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epic <n>`, supports `--json`\n    78→\n    79→### github-import.ts\n    80→Imports GitHub issues labeled for sprint planning into beads. Queries GitHub via `gh` CLI for issues with a specified label (default: `sprint-candidate`), maps GitHub labels to beads type (bug/story/task) and priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids with format `[source:github:owner/repo#N]`.\n    81→- **Key deps:** `lib/github` (isGhAvailable, ghIssueSearch, getRepoFromRemote), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n    82→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--repo <owner/repo>`, `--label <label>`, `--json`\n    83→\n    84→### retry.ts\n    85→Manages retry state for stories. Shows retry counts and flagged-story status, resets counters per-story or globally. Validates story keys against path traversal.\n    86→- **Key deps:** `lib/retry-state` (readRetries, readFlaggedStories, resetRetry), `lib/output`\n    87→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--reset`, `--story <key>`, `--status`, `--json`\n    88→\n    89→### validate.ts\n    90→Runs the self-validation cycle and produces a release gate report. Initializes a validation sprint, loops through `runValidationCycle()` until no actionable ACs remain, then outputs a summary with total/passed/failed/blocked counts and adaptation cycles. Outputs \"RELEASE GATE: PASS -- v1.0 ready\" when all non-blocked ACs pass.\n    91→- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (createValidationSprint, runValidationCycle, getValidationProgress, getACById), `lib/output`\n    92→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--ci` (exit code mode), `--json`\n    93→\n    94→### validate-state.ts\n    95→Validates sprint-state.json consistency against sprint-status.yaml. Thin CLI wrapper that delegates to the sprint module's `validateStateConsistency`.\n    96→- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (validateStateConsistency), `lib/output`\n    97→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--state <path>`, `--sprint-status <path>`\n    98→\n    99→### timeout-report.ts\n   100→Captures diagnostic data from a timed-out iteration. Called by ralph.sh on exit code 124 to preserve git diff, state delta, and partial stderr in a structured markdown report.\n   101→- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (captureTimeoutReport), `lib/output`\n   102→- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--story <key>`, `--iteration <n>`, `--duration <minutes>`, `--output-file <path>`, `--state-snapshot <path>`; supports `--json`\n   103→\n   104→### query.ts\n   105→Queries observability data (logs, metrics, traces) scoped to the current project. Automatically injects service_name filtering into LogsQL and PromQL queries. Resolves endpoints from state (local or remote).\n   106→- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (service name, endpoint resolution)\n   107→- **Subcommands:** `logs <filter>`, `metrics <promql>`, `traces`\n   108→\n   109→### progress.ts\n   110→Updates live run progress in sprint-state.json. Used by harness-run to show real-time story/phase progress during autonomous execution.\n   111→- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (updateRunProgress, clearRunProgress), `lib/output`\n   112→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <key>`, `--phase <phase>`, `--action <text>`, `--ac-progress <text>`, `--clear`, `--json`\n   113→\n   114→### observability-gate.ts\n   115→Checks observability coverage against targets for commit gating. Reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against configurable targets (default: 80% static, 60% runtime). Used by the pre-commit hook to block commits below target.\n   116→- **Key deps:** `modules/observability` (checkObservabilityCoverageGate), `lib/output`\n   117→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--min-static <percent>`, `--min-runtime <percent>`\n   118→\n   119→### audit.ts\n   120→Thin CLI wrapper that registers the `audit` command and delegates to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler. Supports `--json` and `--fix` flags.\n   121→- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit)\n   122→- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--fix`\n   123→\n   124→### verify-env.ts\n   125→Manages the verification environment for black-box story verification. Builds a Docker image from project artifacts (no source code), prepares clean temp workspaces with only story docs, validates the environment, and cleans up.\n   126→- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (buildVerifyImage, prepareVerifyWorkspace, checkVerifyEnv, cleanupVerifyEnv), `lib/output`\n   127→- **Subcommands:** `build` (build Docker image, supports `--json`), `prepare --story <key>` (create clean workspace), `check` (validate image/CLI/otel), `cleanup --story <key>` (remove workspace and container)\n   128→\n   129→## Adding a New Command\n   130→\n   131→1. Create `src/commands/<name>.ts` exporting `register<Name>Command(program: Command): void`\n   132→2. Register in `src/index.ts`, add tests in `src/commands/__tests__/`\n   133→3. Support `--json` output via `cmd.optsWithGlobals().json` and `jsonOutput()` from `lib/output`\n   134→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e5d4728-d8cb-4df9-909c-e75227099f62","uuid":"a29fe67b-75df-4922-baaa-a5a4b1083c92","timestamp":"2026-03-27T06:15:17.149Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/AGENTS.md","content":"# src/commands/\n\nCLI command implementations for the `codeharness` tool. Each file exports a `register*Command(program)` function that adds a command (or command group) to the Commander program instance. All commands are registered in `src/index.ts`.\n\n## Commands\n\n### init.ts\nInitializes the harness in a project. Detects stack (Node.js/Python) and app type, installs dependencies, sets up Beads issue tracking, installs BMAD with patches, creates state file, scaffolds AGENTS.md and docs/, instruments OTLP, and starts the Docker observability stack.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/stack-detect`, `lib/state`, `lib/deps`, `lib/beads`, `lib/bmad`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/templates`, `lib/stack-path`\n- **Subcommands:** none (single action)\n\n### bridge.ts\nBridges BMAD epics/stories into the Beads task store. Parses a BMAD epics markdown file, extracts stories with acceptance criteria, and imports them as Beads issues with deduplication.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/bmad` (parser), `lib/beads` (issue creation), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epics <path>`, supports `--dry-run`\n\n### run.ts\nExecutes the autonomous coding loop. Pre-flight checks: plugin directory, state reconciliation, Docker availability (`isDockerAvailable()`), and orphan container cleanup (`cleanupContainers()`). Then reads sprint status, generates Ralph prompt, and spawns the agent driver with configurable iteration limits, timeouts, and retry counts. Pipes agent stdout/stderr through `driver.parseOutput()` into the Ink renderer.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (isDockerAvailable), `modules/infra` (cleanupContainers), `modules/sprint` (readSprintStatusFromState, reconcileState, getSprintState), `lib/agents` (getDriver), `lib/ink-renderer` (startRenderer), `lib/output`\n- **Exports:** `resolvePluginDir()`, `countStories` (re-export from run-helpers), `registerRunCommand(program)`\n- **Subcommands:** none (single action with many options)\n\n### verify.ts\nRuns the verification pipeline on completed work. Two modes: (1) story verification via `--story <id>` — parses acceptance criteria, checks preconditions, validates proof quality (rejects proofs with PENDING ACs), creates proof document, runs Showboat verify, updates state, closes Beads issue, moves exec-plan to completed; (2) retrospective verification via `--retro --epic <n>` — checks that `epic-N-retrospective.md` exists, marks it done in sprint-status.yaml. JSON output includes `proofQuality` metrics.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (parseStoryACs, validateProofQuality, checkPreconditions, etc.), `lib/doc-health` (exec-plan completion), `lib/beads-sync` (sprint status for retro)\n- **Flags:** `--story <id>` (story mode), `--retro` + `--epic <n>` (retro mode), `--json`\n\n### status.ts\nDisplays current harness status and health. Shows version, stack, enforcement settings, Docker/observability state (mode-aware: local-shared, remote-direct, remote-routed), Beads summary, onboarding progress, session flags, coverage, and verification log. Supports `--check` for pass/fail health checks.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/docker`, `lib/state`, `lib/beads`, `lib/onboard-checks`, `lib/stack-path`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-docker`, `--check`\n\n### onboard.ts\nAlias for `audit` (FR16). Delegates all behavior to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler, ensuring identical output. Provides a deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints a warning before running audit.\n- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit), `lib/output` (warn)\n- **Exports:** `registerOnboardCommand(program)`\n- **Subcommands:** `scan` (deprecated, prints warning then runs audit)\n\n### audit-action.ts\nShared audit action handler used by both `audit.ts` and `onboard.ts`. Contains the full audit execution logic: precondition checks, `runAudit()`, `--fix` handling (generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), and output formatting (human and JSON).\n- **Key deps:** `modules/audit` (runAudit, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), `modules/audit/report` (formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson), `lib/onboard-checks` (runPreconditions), `lib/output`\n- **Exports:** `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean })`\n\n### teardown.ts\nRemoves the harness from a project. Stops Docker containers (mode-aware), removes BMAD patches, cleans OTLP instrumented scripts from package.json, deletes state file and .harness/ cache. Preserves .beads/, _bmad/, and docs/ by default.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/state`, `lib/bmad` (PATCH_TARGETS), `lib/patch-engine`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/stack-path`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--keep-docker`, `--keep-beads`\n\n### state.ts\nManages harness state via subcommands. Provides read/write access to the YAML frontmatter state file using dot-notation keys.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (read/write/get/set), `yaml` (stringify for display)\n- **Subcommands:** `show`, `get <key>`, `set <key> <value>`, `reset-session`\n\n### sync.ts\nSynchronizes Beads issue statuses with story files and sprint-status.yaml. Supports bidirectional, beads-to-files, and files-to-beads directions. Can sync a single story or all stories.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/beads` (issue CRUD), `lib/beads-sync` (sync logic)\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--direction <dir>`, `--story <key>`\n\n### coverage.ts\nRuns tests with coverage measurement and evaluates results against targets. Detects the coverage tool (c8/coverage.py), runs or checks coverage, evaluates against project target, checks per-file coverage floors, and updates state.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/coverage` (detection, execution, evaluation)\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-only`, `--story <id>`, `--min-file <percent>`\n\n### doc-health.ts\nScans documentation for freshness and quality issues. Checks whether AGENTS.md files and other docs are stale relative to their associated source code. Can scope checks to modules changed by a specific story.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/doc-health` (scanning, freshness checks)\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <id>`, `--fix` (placeholder)\n\n### stack.ts\nManages the shared observability stack (Docker-based). Starts, stops, and shows status of the VictoriaMetrics/OTel Collector stack. Mode-aware: handles local-shared, remote-direct, and remote-routed configurations.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (stack lifecycle), `lib/state`, `lib/stack-path`\n- **Subcommands:** `start`, `stop`, `status`\n\n### retro-import.ts\nImports retrospective action items as beads issues. Parses `epic-N-retrospective.md` for action item tables, classifies each item (harness/tool/project), derives priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/retro-parser` (parsing, classification, priority), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epic <n>`, supports `--json`\n\n### github-import.ts\nImports GitHub issues labeled for sprint planning into beads. Queries GitHub via `gh` CLI for issues with a specified label (default: `sprint-candidate`), maps GitHub labels to beads type (bug/story/task) and priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids with format `[source:github:owner/repo#N]`.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/github` (isGhAvailable, ghIssueSearch, getRepoFromRemote), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--repo <owner/repo>`, `--label <label>`, `--json`\n\n### retry.ts\nManages retry state for stories. Shows retry counts and flagged-story status, resets counters per-story or globally. Validates story keys against path traversal.\n- **Key deps:** `lib/retry-state` (readRetries, readFlaggedStories, resetRetry), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--reset`, `--story <key>`, `--status`, `--json`\n\n### validate.ts\nRuns the self-validation cycle and produces a release gate report. Initializes a validation sprint, loops through `runValidationCycle()` until no actionable ACs remain, then outputs a summary with total/passed/failed/blocked counts and adaptation cycles. Outputs \"RELEASE GATE: PASS -- v1.0 ready\" when all non-blocked ACs pass.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (createValidationSprint, runValidationCycle, getValidationProgress, getACById), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--ci` (exit code mode), `--json`\n\n### validate-state.ts\nValidates sprint-state.json consistency against sprint-status.yaml. Thin CLI wrapper that delegates to the sprint module's `validateStateConsistency`.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (validateStateConsistency), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--state <path>`, `--sprint-status <path>`\n\n### timeout-report.ts\nCaptures diagnostic data from a timed-out iteration. Called by ralph.sh on exit code 124 to preserve git diff, state delta, and partial stderr in a structured markdown report.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (captureTimeoutReport), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--story <key>`, `--iteration <n>`, `--duration <minutes>`, `--output-file <path>`, `--state-snapshot <path>`; supports `--json`\n\n### query.ts\nQueries observability data (logs, metrics, traces) scoped to the current project. Automatically injects service_name filtering into LogsQL and PromQL queries. Resolves endpoints from state (local or remote).\n- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (service name, endpoint resolution)\n- **Subcommands:** `logs <filter>`, `metrics <promql>`, `traces`\n\n### progress.ts\nUpdates live run progress in sprint-state.json. Used by harness-run to show real-time story/phase progress during autonomous execution.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (updateRunProgress, clearRunProgress), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <key>`, `--phase <phase>`, `--action <text>`, `--ac-progress <text>`, `--clear`, `--json`\n\n### observability-gate.ts\nChecks observability coverage against targets for commit gating. Reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against configurable targets (default: 80% static, 60% runtime). Used by the pre-commit hook to block commits below target.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/observability` (checkObservabilityCoverageGate), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--min-static <percent>`, `--min-runtime <percent>`\n\n### audit.ts\nThin CLI wrapper that registers the `audit` command and delegates to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler. Supports `--json` and `--fix` flags.\n- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit)\n- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--fix`\n\n### verify-env.ts\nManages the verification environment for black-box story verification. Builds a Docker image from project artifacts (no source code), prepares clean temp workspaces with only story docs, validates the environment, and cleans up.\n- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (buildVerifyImage, prepareVerifyWorkspace, checkVerifyEnv, cleanupVerifyEnv), `lib/output`\n- **Subcommands:** `build` (build Docker image, supports `--json`), `prepare --story <key>` (create clean workspace), `check` (validate image/CLI/otel), `cleanup --story <key>` (remove workspace and container)\n\n## Adding a New Command\n\n1. Create `src/commands/<name>.ts` exporting `register<Name>Command(program: Command): void`\n2. Register in `src/index.ts`, add tests in `src/commands/__tests__/`\n3. Support `--json` output via `cmd.optsWithGlobals().json` and `jsonOutput()` from `lib/output`\n","numLines":134,"startLine":1,"totalLines":134}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SPouVpquv6Tg7U1it536sj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * codeharness stats — Token consumption and cost analysis.\n     3→ * Parses ralph session logs to compute API-equivalent costs by phase, story, tool, and token type.\n     4→ * Outputs human-readable report and optionally writes JSON for retro consumption.\n     5→ */\n     6→\n     7→import { existsSync, readdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n     8→import { join } from 'node:path';\n     9→import { Command } from 'commander';\n    10→import { info, ok, fail, jsonOutput } from '../lib/output.js';\n    11→\n    12→// Opus 4.6 pricing per MTok\n    13→const RATES = {\n    14→  input: 15.0,\n    15→  output: 75.0,\n    16→  cacheRead: 1.50,\n    17→  cacheWrite: 18.75,\n    18→};\n    19→\n    20→interface TokenBucket {\n    21→  input: number;\n    22→  output: number;\n    23→  cacheRead: number;\n    24→  cacheWrite: number;\n    25→  calls: number;\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→function emptyBucket(): TokenBucket {\n    29→  return { input: 0, output: 0, cacheRead: 0, cacheWrite: 0, calls: 0 };\n    30→}\n    31→\n    32→function bucketCost(b: TokenBucket): number {\n    33→  return (b.input * RATES.input + b.output * RATES.output +\n    34→    b.cacheRead * RATES.cacheRead + b.cacheWrite * RATES.cacheWrite) / 1_000_000;\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→function addToBucket(target: TokenBucket, input: number, output: number, cacheRead: number, cacheWrite: number): void {\n    38→  target.input += input;\n    39→  target.output += output;\n    40→  target.cacheRead += cacheRead;\n    41→  target.cacheWrite += cacheWrite;\n    42→  target.calls += 1;\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→interface StatsReport {\n    46→  totalCost: number;\n    47→  totalCalls: number;\n    48→  byPhase: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n    49→  byStory: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n    50→  byTool: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n    51→  byDate: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n    52→  tokenBreakdown: TokenBucket;\n    53→  avgCostPerStory: number;\n    54→  storiesTracked: number;\n    55→}\n    56→\n    57→function parseLogFile(filePath: string, report: {\n    58→  byPhase: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n    59→  byStory: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n    60→  byTool: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n    61→  byDate: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n    62→  messages: Array<{ input: number; output: number; cacheRead: number; cacheWrite: number; phase: string; story: string; tool: string }>;\n    63→}): void {\n    64→  const basename = filePath.split('/').pop() ?? '';\n    65→  const dateMatch = basename.match(/(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})/);\n    66→  const date = dateMatch ? dateMatch[1] : 'unknown';\n    67→\n    68→  let currentPhase = 'orchestrator';\n    69→  let currentStory = 'unknown';\n    70→  let currentTool = '';\n    71→  let msgInput = 0;\n    72→  let msgOutput = 0;\n    73→  let msgCacheRead = 0;\n    74→  let msgCacheWrite = 0;\n    75→\n    76→  const content = readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8');\n    77→  for (const line of content.split('\\n')) {\n    78→    if (!line.startsWith('{')) continue;\n    79→    let d: Record<string, unknown>;\n    80→    try { d = JSON.parse(line) as Record<string, unknown>; } catch { continue; } // IGNORE: skip malformed JSON lines in logs\n    81→\n    82→    const typ = d.type as string;\n    83→\n    84→    if (typ === 'stream_event') {\n    85→      const evt = d.event as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n    86→      if (!evt) continue;\n    87→      const evtType = evt.type as string;\n    88→\n    89→      if (evtType === 'message_start') {\n    90→        // Record previous message\n    91→        if (msgInput + msgOutput + msgCacheRead + msgCacheWrite > 0) {\n    92→          report.messages.push({ input: msgInput, output: msgOutput, cacheRead: msgCacheRead, cacheWrite: msgCacheWrite, phase: currentPhase, story: currentStory, tool: currentTool });\n    93→        }\n    94→        const usage = ((evt.message as Record<string, unknown>)?.usage ?? {}) as Record<string, number>;\n    95→        msgInput = usage.input_tokens ?? 0;\n    96→        msgCacheRead = usage.cache_read_input_tokens ?? 0;\n    97→        msgCacheWrite = usage.cache_creation_input_tokens ?? 0;\n    98→        msgOutput = 0;\n    99→      } else if (evtType === 'message_delta') {\n   100→        const usage = (evt.usage ?? {}) as Record<string, number>;\n   101→        msgOutput += usage.output_tokens ?? 0;\n   102→      } else if (evtType === 'content_block_start') {\n   103→        const cb = evt.content_block as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n   104→        if (cb?.type === 'tool_use') currentTool = (cb.name as string) ?? '';\n   105→      } else if (evtType === 'content_block_delta') {\n   106→        const text = ((evt.delta as Record<string, unknown>)?.text as string) ?? '';\n   107→        // Detect phase from harness-run text output\n   108→        if (text.includes('Step 3a') || text.toLowerCase().includes('create-story')) currentPhase = 'create-story';\n   109→        else if (text.includes('Step 3b') || text.toLowerCase().includes('dev-story')) currentPhase = 'dev-story';\n   110→        else if (text.includes('Step 3c') || text.toLowerCase().includes('code-review') || text.toLowerCase().includes('code review')) currentPhase = 'code-review';\n   111→        else if (text.includes('Step 3d') || text.toLowerCase().includes('verif')) currentPhase = 'verify';\n   112→        else if (text.includes('Step 8') || text.toLowerCase().includes('retro')) currentPhase = 'retro';\n   113→        // Detect story\n   114→        const sm = text.match(/(\\d+-\\d+-[a-z][\\w-]*)/);\n   115→        if (sm) currentStory = sm[1];\n   116→      }\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    // Detect phase from subagent descriptions\n   120→    if (typ === 'system' && (d.subtype as string) === 'task_started') {\n   121→      const desc = ((d.description as string) ?? '').toLowerCase();\n   122→      if (desc.includes('code review') || desc.includes('code-review')) currentPhase = 'code-review';\n   123→      else if (desc.includes('dev-story') || desc.includes('dev story') || desc.includes('implement')) currentPhase = 'dev-story';\n   124→      else if (desc.includes('create-story') || desc.includes('create story')) currentPhase = 'create-story';\n   125→      else if (desc.includes('verif')) currentPhase = 'verify';\n   126→      else if (desc.includes('retro')) currentPhase = 'retro';\n   127→    }\n   128→  }\n   129→\n   130→  // Record last message\n   131→  if (msgInput + msgOutput + msgCacheRead + msgCacheWrite > 0) {\n   132→    report.messages.push({ input: msgInput, output: msgOutput, cacheRead: msgCacheRead, cacheWrite: msgCacheWrite, phase: currentPhase, story: currentStory, tool: currentTool });\n   133→  }\n   134→}\n   135→\n   136→function generateReport(projectDir: string): StatsReport {\n   137→  const logsDir = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'logs');\n   138→  const logFiles = readdirSync(logsDir)\n   139→    .filter(f => f.startsWith('claude_output_') && f.endsWith('.log'))\n   140→    .sort()\n   141→    .map(f => join(logsDir, f));\n   142→\n   143→  const report = {\n   144→    byPhase: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n   145→    byStory: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n   146→    byTool: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n   147→    byDate: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n   148→    messages: [] as Array<{ input: number; output: number; cacheRead: number; cacheWrite: number; phase: string; story: string; tool: string }>,\n   149→  };\n   150→\n   151→  for (const logFile of logFiles) {\n   152→    parseLogFile(logFile, report);\n   153→  }\n   154→\n   155→  // Aggregate messages into buckets\n   156→  const byPhase: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n   157→  const byStory: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n   158→  const byTool: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n   159→  const total = emptyBucket();\n   160→\n   161→  for (const msg of report.messages) {\n   162→    if (!byPhase[msg.phase]) byPhase[msg.phase] = emptyBucket();\n   163→    addToBucket(byPhase[msg.phase], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n   164→    if (!byStory[msg.story]) byStory[msg.story] = emptyBucket();\n   165→    addToBucket(byStory[msg.story], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n   166→    if (msg.tool) {\n   167→      if (!byTool[msg.tool]) byTool[msg.tool] = emptyBucket();\n   168→      addToBucket(byTool[msg.tool], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n   169→    }\n   170→    addToBucket(total, msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n   171→  }\n   172→\n   173→  const storyKeys = Object.keys(byStory).filter(k => /^\\d+-\\d+-/.test(k));\n   174→  const totalCost = bucketCost(total);\n   175→  const avgCostPerStory = storyKeys.length > 0\n   176→    ? storyKeys.reduce((sum, k) => sum + bucketCost(byStory[k]), 0) / storyKeys.length\n   177→    : 0;\n   178→\n   179→  return {\n   180→    totalCost,\n   181→    totalCalls: report.messages.length,\n   182→    byPhase,\n   183→    byStory,\n   184→    byTool,\n   185→    byDate: {},\n   186→    tokenBreakdown: total,\n   187→    avgCostPerStory,\n   188→    storiesTracked: storyKeys.length,\n   189→  };\n   190→}\n   191→\n   192→function formatReport(report: StatsReport): string {\n   193→  const lines: string[] = [];\n   194→  lines.push('# Harness Cost Report');\n   195→  lines.push('');\n   196→  lines.push(`Total API-equivalent cost: $${report.totalCost.toFixed(2)}`);\n   197→  lines.push(`Total API calls: ${report.totalCalls}`);\n   198→  lines.push(`Average cost per story: $${report.avgCostPerStory.toFixed(2)} (${report.storiesTracked} stories)`);\n   199→  lines.push('');\n   200→\n   201→  // Token type breakdown\n   202→  const tb = report.tokenBreakdown;\n   203→  lines.push('## Cost by Token Type');\n   204→  lines.push('');\n   205→  lines.push(`| Type | Tokens | Rate | Cost | % |`);\n   206→  lines.push(`|------|--------|------|------|---|`);\n   207→  const crCost = tb.cacheRead * RATES.cacheRead / 1e6;\n   208→  const cwCost = tb.cacheWrite * RATES.cacheWrite / 1e6;\n   209→  const outCost = tb.output * RATES.output / 1e6;\n   210→  const inpCost = tb.input * RATES.input / 1e6;\n   211→  lines.push(`| Cache reads | ${tb.cacheRead.toLocaleString()} | $1.50/MTok | $${crCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(crCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n   212→  lines.push(`| Cache writes | ${tb.cacheWrite.toLocaleString()} | $18.75/MTok | $${cwCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(cwCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n   213→  lines.push(`| Output | ${tb.output.toLocaleString()} | $75/MTok | $${outCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(outCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n   214→  lines.push(`| Input | ${tb.input.toLocaleString()} | $15/MTok | $${inpCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(inpCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n   215→  lines.push('');\n   216→\n   217→  // By phase\n   218→  lines.push('## Cost by Phase');\n   219→  lines.push('');\n   220→  lines.push(`| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n   221→  lines.push(`|-------|-------|------|---|`);\n   222→  const sortedPhases = Object.entries(report.byPhase).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n   223→  for (const [phase, bucket] of sortedPhases) {\n   224→    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n   225→    lines.push(`| ${phase} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n   226→  }\n   227→  lines.push('');\n   228→\n   229→  // By tool\n   230→  lines.push('## Cost by Tool');\n   231→  lines.push('');\n   232→  lines.push(`| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n   233→  lines.push(`|------|-------|------|---|`);\n   234→  const sortedTools = Object.entries(report.byTool).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n   235→  for (const [tool, bucket] of sortedTools.slice(0, 10)) {\n   236→    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n   237→    lines.push(`| ${tool} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n   238→  }\n   239→  lines.push('');\n   240→\n   241→  // Top stories\n   242→  lines.push('## Top 10 Most Expensive Stories');\n   243→  lines.push('');\n   244→  lines.push(`| Story | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n   245→  lines.push(`|-------|-------|------|---|`);\n   246→  const sortedStories = Object.entries(report.byStory).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n   247→  for (const [story, bucket] of sortedStories.slice(0, 10)) {\n   248→    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n   249→    lines.push(`| ${story} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n   250→  }\n   251→\n   252→  return lines.join('\\n');\n   253→}\n   254→\n   255→export function registerStatsCommand(program: Command): void {\n   256→  program\n   257→    .command('stats')\n   258→    .description('Analyze token consumption and cost from ralph session logs')\n   259→    .option('--save', 'Save report to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md')\n   260→    .action((options, cmd) => {\n   261→      const globalOpts = cmd.optsWithGlobals();\n   262→      const isJson = !!globalOpts.json;\n   263→      const projectDir = process.cwd();\n   264→      const logsDir = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'logs');\n   265→\n   266→      if (!existsSync(logsDir)) {\n   267→        fail('No ralph/logs/ directory found — run codeharness run first');\n   268→        process.exitCode = 1;\n   269→        return;\n   270→      }\n   271→\n   272→      const report = generateReport(projectDir);\n   273→\n   274→      if (isJson) {\n   275→        jsonOutput(report as unknown as Record<string, unknown>);\n   276→        return;\n   277→      }\n   278→\n   279→      const formatted = formatReport(report);\n   280→      console.log(formatted);\n   281→\n   282→      if (options.save) {\n   283→        const outPath = join(projectDir, '_bmad-output', 'implementation-artifacts', 'cost-report.md');\n   284→        writeFileSync(outPath, formatted, 'utf-8');\n   285→        ok(`Report saved to ${outPath}`);\n   286→      }\n   287→    });\n   288→}\n   289→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e5d4728-d8cb-4df9-909c-e75227099f62","uuid":"1c87c159-4c12-4d4c-a9aa-190ecedb7d37","timestamp":"2026-03-27T06:15:17.277Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/stats.ts","content":"/**\n * codeharness stats — Token consumption and cost analysis.\n * Parses ralph session logs to compute API-equivalent costs by phase, story, tool, and token type.\n * Outputs human-readable report and optionally writes JSON for retro consumption.\n */\n\nimport { existsSync, readdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { join } from 'node:path';\nimport { Command } from 'commander';\nimport { info, ok, fail, jsonOutput } from '../lib/output.js';\n\n// Opus 4.6 pricing per MTok\nconst RATES = {\n  input: 15.0,\n  output: 75.0,\n  cacheRead: 1.50,\n  cacheWrite: 18.75,\n};\n\ninterface TokenBucket {\n  input: number;\n  output: number;\n  cacheRead: number;\n  cacheWrite: number;\n  calls: number;\n}\n\nfunction emptyBucket(): TokenBucket {\n  return { input: 0, output: 0, cacheRead: 0, cacheWrite: 0, calls: 0 };\n}\n\nfunction bucketCost(b: TokenBucket): number {\n  return (b.input * RATES.input + b.output * RATES.output +\n    b.cacheRead * RATES.cacheRead + b.cacheWrite * RATES.cacheWrite) / 1_000_000;\n}\n\nfunction addToBucket(target: TokenBucket, input: number, output: number, cacheRead: number, cacheWrite: number): void {\n  target.input += input;\n  target.output += output;\n  target.cacheRead += cacheRead;\n  target.cacheWrite += cacheWrite;\n  target.calls += 1;\n}\n\ninterface StatsReport {\n  totalCost: number;\n  totalCalls: number;\n  byPhase: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byStory: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byTool: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byDate: Record<string, TokenBucket>;\n  tokenBreakdown: TokenBucket;\n  avgCostPerStory: number;\n  storiesTracked: number;\n}\n\nfunction parseLogFile(filePath: string, report: {\n  byPhase: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byStory: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byTool: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n  byDate: Map<string, TokenBucket>;\n  messages: Array<{ input: number; output: number; cacheRead: number; cacheWrite: number; phase: string; story: string; tool: string }>;\n}): void {\n  const basename = filePath.split('/').pop() ?? '';\n  const dateMatch = basename.match(/(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})/);\n  const date = dateMatch ? dateMatch[1] : 'unknown';\n\n  let currentPhase = 'orchestrator';\n  let currentStory = 'unknown';\n  let currentTool = '';\n  let msgInput = 0;\n  let msgOutput = 0;\n  let msgCacheRead = 0;\n  let msgCacheWrite = 0;\n\n  const content = readFileSync(filePath, 'utf-8');\n  for (const line of content.split('\\n')) {\n    if (!line.startsWith('{')) continue;\n    let d: Record<string, unknown>;\n    try { d = JSON.parse(line) as Record<string, unknown>; } catch { continue; } // IGNORE: skip malformed JSON lines in logs\n\n    const typ = d.type as string;\n\n    if (typ === 'stream_event') {\n      const evt = d.event as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n      if (!evt) continue;\n      const evtType = evt.type as string;\n\n      if (evtType === 'message_start') {\n        // Record previous message\n        if (msgInput + msgOutput + msgCacheRead + msgCacheWrite > 0) {\n          report.messages.push({ input: msgInput, output: msgOutput, cacheRead: msgCacheRead, cacheWrite: msgCacheWrite, phase: currentPhase, story: currentStory, tool: currentTool });\n        }\n        const usage = ((evt.message as Record<string, unknown>)?.usage ?? {}) as Record<string, number>;\n        msgInput = usage.input_tokens ?? 0;\n        msgCacheRead = usage.cache_read_input_tokens ?? 0;\n        msgCacheWrite = usage.cache_creation_input_tokens ?? 0;\n        msgOutput = 0;\n      } else if (evtType === 'message_delta') {\n        const usage = (evt.usage ?? {}) as Record<string, number>;\n        msgOutput += usage.output_tokens ?? 0;\n      } else if (evtType === 'content_block_start') {\n        const cb = evt.content_block as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;\n        if (cb?.type === 'tool_use') currentTool = (cb.name as string) ?? '';\n      } else if (evtType === 'content_block_delta') {\n        const text = ((evt.delta as Record<string, unknown>)?.text as string) ?? '';\n        // Detect phase from harness-run text output\n        if (text.includes('Step 3a') || text.toLowerCase().includes('create-story')) currentPhase = 'create-story';\n        else if (text.includes('Step 3b') || text.toLowerCase().includes('dev-story')) currentPhase = 'dev-story';\n        else if (text.includes('Step 3c') || text.toLowerCase().includes('code-review') || text.toLowerCase().includes('code review')) currentPhase = 'code-review';\n        else if (text.includes('Step 3d') || text.toLowerCase().includes('verif')) currentPhase = 'verify';\n        else if (text.includes('Step 8') || text.toLowerCase().includes('retro')) currentPhase = 'retro';\n        // Detect story\n        const sm = text.match(/(\\d+-\\d+-[a-z][\\w-]*)/);\n        if (sm) currentStory = sm[1];\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Detect phase from subagent descriptions\n    if (typ === 'system' && (d.subtype as string) === 'task_started') {\n      const desc = ((d.description as string) ?? '').toLowerCase();\n      if (desc.includes('code review') || desc.includes('code-review')) currentPhase = 'code-review';\n      else if (desc.includes('dev-story') || desc.includes('dev story') || desc.includes('implement')) currentPhase = 'dev-story';\n      else if (desc.includes('create-story') || desc.includes('create story')) currentPhase = 'create-story';\n      else if (desc.includes('verif')) currentPhase = 'verify';\n      else if (desc.includes('retro')) currentPhase = 'retro';\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Record last message\n  if (msgInput + msgOutput + msgCacheRead + msgCacheWrite > 0) {\n    report.messages.push({ input: msgInput, output: msgOutput, cacheRead: msgCacheRead, cacheWrite: msgCacheWrite, phase: currentPhase, story: currentStory, tool: currentTool });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction generateReport(projectDir: string): StatsReport {\n  const logsDir = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'logs');\n  const logFiles = readdirSync(logsDir)\n    .filter(f => f.startsWith('claude_output_') && f.endsWith('.log'))\n    .sort()\n    .map(f => join(logsDir, f));\n\n  const report = {\n    byPhase: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n    byStory: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n    byTool: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n    byDate: new Map<string, TokenBucket>(),\n    messages: [] as Array<{ input: number; output: number; cacheRead: number; cacheWrite: number; phase: string; story: string; tool: string }>,\n  };\n\n  for (const logFile of logFiles) {\n    parseLogFile(logFile, report);\n  }\n\n  // Aggregate messages into buckets\n  const byPhase: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n  const byStory: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n  const byTool: Record<string, TokenBucket> = {};\n  const total = emptyBucket();\n\n  for (const msg of report.messages) {\n    if (!byPhase[msg.phase]) byPhase[msg.phase] = emptyBucket();\n    addToBucket(byPhase[msg.phase], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n    if (!byStory[msg.story]) byStory[msg.story] = emptyBucket();\n    addToBucket(byStory[msg.story], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n    if (msg.tool) {\n      if (!byTool[msg.tool]) byTool[msg.tool] = emptyBucket();\n      addToBucket(byTool[msg.tool], msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n    }\n    addToBucket(total, msg.input, msg.output, msg.cacheRead, msg.cacheWrite);\n  }\n\n  const storyKeys = Object.keys(byStory).filter(k => /^\\d+-\\d+-/.test(k));\n  const totalCost = bucketCost(total);\n  const avgCostPerStory = storyKeys.length > 0\n    ? storyKeys.reduce((sum, k) => sum + bucketCost(byStory[k]), 0) / storyKeys.length\n    : 0;\n\n  return {\n    totalCost,\n    totalCalls: report.messages.length,\n    byPhase,\n    byStory,\n    byTool,\n    byDate: {},\n    tokenBreakdown: total,\n    avgCostPerStory,\n    storiesTracked: storyKeys.length,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction formatReport(report: StatsReport): string {\n  const lines: string[] = [];\n  lines.push('# Harness Cost Report');\n  lines.push('');\n  lines.push(`Total API-equivalent cost: $${report.totalCost.toFixed(2)}`);\n  lines.push(`Total API calls: ${report.totalCalls}`);\n  lines.push(`Average cost per story: $${report.avgCostPerStory.toFixed(2)} (${report.storiesTracked} stories)`);\n  lines.push('');\n\n  // Token type breakdown\n  const tb = report.tokenBreakdown;\n  lines.push('## Cost by Token Type');\n  lines.push('');\n  lines.push(`| Type | Tokens | Rate | Cost | % |`);\n  lines.push(`|------|--------|------|------|---|`);\n  const crCost = tb.cacheRead * RATES.cacheRead / 1e6;\n  const cwCost = tb.cacheWrite * RATES.cacheWrite / 1e6;\n  const outCost = tb.output * RATES.output / 1e6;\n  const inpCost = tb.input * RATES.input / 1e6;\n  lines.push(`| Cache reads | ${tb.cacheRead.toLocaleString()} | $1.50/MTok | $${crCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(crCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n  lines.push(`| Cache writes | ${tb.cacheWrite.toLocaleString()} | $18.75/MTok | $${cwCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(cwCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n  lines.push(`| Output | ${tb.output.toLocaleString()} | $75/MTok | $${outCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(outCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n  lines.push(`| Input | ${tb.input.toLocaleString()} | $15/MTok | $${inpCost.toFixed(2)} | ${(inpCost / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(0)}% |`);\n  lines.push('');\n\n  // By phase\n  lines.push('## Cost by Phase');\n  lines.push('');\n  lines.push(`| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n  lines.push(`|-------|-------|------|---|`);\n  const sortedPhases = Object.entries(report.byPhase).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n  for (const [phase, bucket] of sortedPhases) {\n    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n    lines.push(`| ${phase} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n  }\n  lines.push('');\n\n  // By tool\n  lines.push('## Cost by Tool');\n  lines.push('');\n  lines.push(`| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n  lines.push(`|------|-------|------|---|`);\n  const sortedTools = Object.entries(report.byTool).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n  for (const [tool, bucket] of sortedTools.slice(0, 10)) {\n    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n    lines.push(`| ${tool} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n  }\n  lines.push('');\n\n  // Top stories\n  lines.push('## Top 10 Most Expensive Stories');\n  lines.push('');\n  lines.push(`| Story | Calls | Cost | % |`);\n  lines.push(`|-------|-------|------|---|`);\n  const sortedStories = Object.entries(report.byStory).sort((a, b) => bucketCost(b[1]) - bucketCost(a[1]));\n  for (const [story, bucket] of sortedStories.slice(0, 10)) {\n    const c = bucketCost(bucket);\n    lines.push(`| ${story} | ${bucket.calls} | $${c.toFixed(2)} | ${(c / report.totalCost * 100).toFixed(1)}% |`);\n  }\n\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function registerStatsCommand(program: Command): void {\n  program\n    .command('stats')\n    .description('Analyze token consumption and cost from ralph session logs')\n    .option('--save', 'Save report to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md')\n    .action((options, cmd) => {\n      const globalOpts = cmd.optsWithGlobals();\n      const isJson = !!globalOpts.json;\n      const projectDir = process.cwd();\n      const logsDir = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'logs');\n\n      if (!existsSync(logsDir)) {\n        fail('No ralph/logs/ directory found — run codeharness run first');\n        process.exitCode = 1;\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const report = generateReport(projectDir);\n\n      if (isJson) {\n        jsonOutput(report as unknown as Record<string, unknown>);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const formatted = formatReport(report);\n      console.log(formatted);\n\n      if (options.save) {\n        const outPath = join(projectDir, '_bmad-output', 'implementation-artifacts', 'cost-report.md');\n        writeFileSync(outPath, formatted, 'utf-8');\n        ok(`Report saved to ${outPath}`);\n      }\n    });\n}\n","numLines":289,"startLine":1,"totalLines":289}}}
